text: I know we passed it already, but gates in EDH are hilarious. Last weekend at the GP, it was the deck I won most often with, which is sort of crazy

I use it as an excuse to run a bunch of pet cards and super janky cycles
<@UGK9N4JJ2> You adding Serra to REki?

<@U4V5EHQ2G>, Djeru? I’m thinking about it. She is definitely going into Jeskies, but I think she might find a place in Djeru. Having Worship as an emblem seems really strong and relatively easy to do in the deck. What were you thinking on your end?
Oops, yeah Djeru
Proliferate has been really strong, so I've been leaning into walkers that abuse that, go I'm gonna swap Gideon Champion of Justice for her since it's hard to ult him out of the blue.
Generous Gift has actually been the tricky one deciding between Oblation and Return to Dust

I’m glad to hear that! I haven’t had much time to play him since WAR dropped. I know I had initially cut Champion of Justice, but I think I may have added him back in. It seems like a reasonable swap.

I run a bunch of boardwipes and some Orings in my Deck, so I’m not sure if I’m going to add gift. I also cut Return to Dust for Crush Contraband when Guilds dropped.
I have Crush in the deck still, and that makes RtD easier to lose. I just flex Oblation too much as a draw spell
Is an Altar’s Reap that good when your commander can tutor up Karn or Ugin to draw you cards? Not being sassy, genuine question. I’ve always values Oblation quite low

If it just did that, no, but the fact that it can do that if I'm desperate or someone goes to kill a walker I want back in my library, plus it also deals with almost any threat makes it worth. I've stopped a Sneak Attack'ed Blightsteel with it recently, and used it on my own Karn someone was hitting with Utter End, then just got him again and recast him next turn after drawing two. The utility is worth I think.

That’s fair. I’m running Mistveil Plains, but I didn’t think about the fact that if you target your own walkers, Djeru can search them up. That’s a great point, I think you may have sold me on it for the deck
Mistveil Plains does a lot of work in the deck
Yeah, which is why I’m so shocked I didn’t think of Oblation’s implications :joy:
It's one of the few decks where the tuck effect is probably better for you than a simple destroy/sacrifice
100%. I shifted from [[Yomiji]] and [[Profound Journey]] effects to things like Mistveil Plains. Shuffling + Djeru is deceptively powerful
